ussion Summary:**\\nThe initial question led to an investigation of the project's file system for references to `@tests/`. Upon finding no direct usage, the explanation shifted to the general concept of path aliases, particularly relevant in JavaScript/TypeScript projects, where `@tests/` often serves as an alias pointing to a `tests/` directory to simplify imports.\\n\\n---\\n*Auto-generated by ByteRover CipherAgent on 2025-11-16 12:11:17*\",\"filePath\":\"programming-topics-20251116-121117.md\"}",
